# Project Conventions

Refer to `CONVENTIONS.md` at the workspace root for the full specification.

## Project Structure

Every project must have: `README.md`, `paper/`, `codes/`. Inside `codes/`: `core/`, `solvers/`, `problems/`, `experiments/`, `tests/`, `utils/`, `scripts/`, `results/`, `plans/`.

## Naming Rules

- Directories: `lowercase_snake_case` (e.g., `bup_newuoa/`, `dfo_tr/`)
- Python files: `lowercase_snake_case.py`
- Solver main: `{algorithm}.py`; versions: `{algorithm}_v{N}.py`
- Test files: `test_{module}.py`
- LaTeX papers: `{project}_paper_v{major}_{minor}.tex`
- Exploratory scripts: prefix with `_` (e.g., `_test_v7_quick.py`)

## Python Style

- PEP 8, line length 100, 4-space indent
- NumPy-style docstrings on public APIs
- Imports: stdlib / third-party / local (blank-line separated)
- Classes: `PascalCase`; functions/variables: `snake_case`; constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`

## Cross-Platform (CRITICAL)

- ALWAYS use `pathlib.Path` for paths, NEVER hardcode `\` or `/`
- sys.path setup: `_CODES_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parents[N]`
- Create dirs with `Path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)`
- When passing paths to libraries (matplotlib, pandas): use `str(path)`
- Every project must have `.gitattributes` with `* text=auto eol=lf`

## File Placement

- New solvers go in `codes/solvers/{algorithm_name}/`
- New experiments go in `codes/experiments/{benchmarks|ablation|analysis|research}/`
- Results go in `codes/results/{experiment_name}/` with `REPORT.md`
- Helper scripts go in `codes/scripts/`
- Plans and checklists go in `codes/plans/`

## Git: What to Track

- TRACK: `.py`, `.csv`, `.json`, `.xls`, `.xlsx`, `.md`, `.tex`, `.txt`
- DO NOT TRACK: `.pdf`, `.png`, `.jpg`, `.eps`, `.svg` (generated figures)
- Exception: `paper/**/*.pdf` and `paper/**/*.png` ARE tracked
- Figures are regenerated locally by running plotting scripts

## Experiment Structure

- Fixed seeds: `SEEDS = [42, 123, 7, 256, 999]`
- Default opts: `{"max_eval": 3000, "rhobeg": 1.0, "rhoend": 1e-8}`
- Success metric: More-Wild relative error
- Save raw data to CSV; figures generated separately and not committed

## Figure Regeneration

- Generated figures (PDF, PNG, etc.) are NOT in Git -- they must be regenerated locally
- After cloning, run the project's replot script from `codes/`:
  - BUPTR: `python scripts/replot_from_csv.py`
  - DisGRem: `python scripts/replot.py`
- Every experiment producing figures MUST have a companion plotting script
- Plotting scripts must be self-contained: CSV data in → figures out
- Paper figures live in `paper/` and ARE tracked by Git

## Cloning & Syncing

- Repos: `git clone https://github.com/huwei0121/{BUPTR|DFOETR|DisGRem}.git`
- After clone: `cd <project>/codes && python -m venv .venv && pip install -r requirements.txt`
- Then regenerate figures: `python scripts/replot_from_csv.py` (or project-specific script)
- Daily workflow: `git pull` before working, `git add -A && git commit && git push` after
